The South African Weather Service (Saws) has warned of severe thunderstorms expected in western parts of KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday. The weather office said scattered showers and thundershowers are expected in the western and southern parts of KZN. These thunderstorms are expected to become severe and be accompanied by hail, excessive lightning and heavy downpours. Saws said the weather conditions are expected to lead to localised flooding. Residents are urged to take caution or avoid travelling on bridges and roads in low lying areas as these may be susceptible to flooding and there may be sinkholes. Areas expected to be affected include Alfred Duma - Indaka, Alfred Duma - Ladysmith, Dannhauser, Dr N. Dlamini-Zuma - Underberg, eMadlangeni, Endumeni, Greater Kokstad, Impendle, Ingwe, Inkosi Langalibalele - Estcourt, Inkosi Langalibalele - Sobabili, Mpofana - Giants Castle, Mpofana - Mooi River, Newcastle, Okhahlamba, Ray Nkonyeni, Richmond, Msunduzi, Ubuhlebezwe, uMngeni, UMuziwabantu, Umzimkhulu and Umzumbe. 